{
    "attributes": {
        "action": "Base Extended Producer Responsibility fees for packaging on units not weight",
        "additional_details": "The weight-based fee structure disproportionately impacts businesses using glass despite it being one of the most sustainable and safest packaging materials available.\r\nWe believe the current EPR model:\r\n- Drives up costs for businesses and consumers during a cost-of-living crisis\r\n- Pushes companies to switch to less sustainable materials\r\n- Gives an advantage to imported glass with higher carbon footprints",
        "background": "In its current format, the EPR regulations disproportionately impact businesses using glass. We think the regulations should be changed from a weight-based fee structure to a unit-based one to help towards the UK's Net Zero Goals.",
